TITLE: CVS nurse fired after refusing to prescribe birth control over religious beliefs sues pharmacy
SUMMARY: A former nurse practitioner for CVS claimed she had been discriminated against for her religious beliefs in a lawsuit filed against the company Wednesday after she had been fired for refusing to prescribe birth control

TITLE: Larry Kudlow: The era of 4000 page omnibus spending bills is over
SUMMARY: FOX Business host Larry Kudlow discusses the government's debt limit and ceiling and the GOP's movement to restore a regular budget order on 'Kudlow

TITLE: Million Dollar Listing's Josh Flagg: Housing market nothing like 2008
SUMMARY: Million Dollar Listing Los Angeles cast member and real estate broker Josh Flagg discusses if real estate is shifting in favor of the homebuyer on 'The Claman Countdown

TITLE: Crypto.com cuts 20% of staff, citing economic hurdles and FTX collapse
SUMMARY: Crypto.com cuts hundreds of workers in the wake of rival FTX's collapse. A lack of faith in future cryptocurrency markets has sent valuations tumbling

TITLE: Bank of America CEO sees 'mild recession' in 2023 and is preparing for worse
SUMMARY: The U.S. economy is likely headed for a recession in 2023, according to Bank of America CEO Brian Moynihan, who is preparing for a mild downturn this year

TITLE: US debt ceiling will require Treasury 'extraordinary measures' to avoid default
SUMMARY: With the U.S. on track to hit the debt ceiling limit next week, Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen warns 'extraordinary measures' will be taken to navigate the crisis

TITLE: Tesla owners feel 'duped' after company slashes prices
SUMMARY: Many Tesla owners are voicing frustration after CEO Elon Musk announced significant price slashes to the massively popular electric cars

TITLE: New York airport close call between two passenger planes on runway under investigation
SUMMARY: The FAA and NTSB are investigating a close call between two planes on a runway at JFK International Airport in New York City around 8:45 p.m. on Friday evening

TITLE: Economic optimism has 'collapsed' globally, survey finds
SUMMARY: The 2023 Edelman Trust Barometer found economic optimism across the globe has suffered a "massive collapse," with most developed nations reporting all-time lows

TITLE: Frontier Airlines launches all-you-can-fly summer pass for $399
SUMMARY: Low-cost Frontier Airlines has announced a new $399 all-you-can-fly pass allowing travelers to book unlimited flights to domestic and international destinations over the summer

TITLE: Private sector job growth cools to 106,000 in January, lowest in 2 years: ADP
SUMMARY: Private U.S. companies added just 106,000 new workers in January as weather-related issues, including severe flooding across California, disrupted hiring

TITLE: As Tesla ignites an EV price war, suppliers brace for Musk seeking givebacks
SUMMARY: Most Tesla suppliers, which include battery makers Panasonic, LG Energy Solution, and CATL, as well as Italian casting machine maker IDRA Group, avoid discussing the carmaker publicly

TITLE: US manufacturing sector sinks further in January
SUMMARY: The ISM survey's forward-looking new orders sub-index plunged to 42.5 in January from 45.1 in December. It was the fifth straight month that this measure has contracted

TITLE: EV maker Rivian cutting 6% of workforce, but manufacturing jobs spared
SUMMARY: Electric vehicle maker Rivian Automotive announced that it will lay off about 6% of its workforce amid a push to cut costs and reach profitability in a competitive EV market

TITLE: Fed raises interest rates by a quarter point but signals inflation fight's not over
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday enacted its eighth consecutive interest rate hike as it attempts to cool inflation without triggering an economic recession

TITLE: US return-to-office rate rises above 50% for first time since pandemic began
SUMMARY: Office use at 50.4% in survey of 10 major US cities. In a blow to remote-work, office use climbed above 50% for the first time since the coronavirus pandemic began

TITLE: Rand Paul: Republicans and Democrats' proposals won't balance the budget
SUMMARY: Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., shares his strategy to balance America's budget and slams Dr. Fauci's handling of the COVID-19 pandemic on 'The Evening Edit

TITLE: Hurricane Ian aftermath: Boat recoveries ongoing in Southwest Florida
SUMMARY: Four months after Hurricane Ian, homeowners and business owners are still struggling to remove boats that traveled several miles during the storm

TITLE: Biden's fantasy economy: Americans see through SOTU spin on jobs, inflation, deficits
SUMMARY: President Biden tried to take credit for what he claims is an improving economy durin ghis State of the Union speech Tuesday night. Americans aren't falling for it

TITLE: Jamie Dimon warns it's too early to declare victory against inflation
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve may be forced to raise interest rates higher than expected if high inflation persists, according to JPMorgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon

TITLE: Pilot shortage puts pressure on airline operations
SUMMARY: The pilot shortage is most severe at small, regional airlines, but it could spread to the major carriers. The U.S. has the strictest standards to qualify as a pilot

TITLE: SNAP emergency food benefits ending for millions of residents
SUMMARY: Residents of many states who rely on federal assistance to buy food will see benefits shrink when COVID-related emergency allotments come to an end by March

TITLE: Used-car prices unexpectedly spike again as inflation fears return
SUMMARY: Used-vehicle prices rose in January at the fastest monthly pace since 2021, a sign that underlying inflationary pressures in the economy remain strong

TITLE: Inflation has a 75% chance of rebounding or remaining high, top economist warns
SUMMARY: Top economist Mohamed El-Erian forecasts a high chance of inflation in the U.S. economy remaining abnormally high this year, despite the Fed's rate hikes

TITLE: Oil prices jump after Russia announces it will slash production
SUMMARY: Russia announced Friday that it plans to cut oil production by 5%, or 500,000 barrels, beginning in March, sending Brent crude prices soaring higher

TITLE: Rioters take to streets in France over Macron's pension plan
SUMMARY: Demonstrations broke out across France on Saturday in opposition to proposed legislation that would increase the minimum retirement age for full state pension from 62 to 64
